23 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Title.
24 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Babies at School Act".
25
26 SECTION 2. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative findings and intent.
27 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
28 (1) A parent or guardian who is a school employee has a
29 responsibility to both his or her job and his or her family; and
30 (2) The first six (6) months of a child's life poses heightened
31 demands of a parent.
32 (b) This act is intended to increase school employee retention by
33 allowing schools to permit a parent or legal guardian who is a school
34 employee to bring his or her infant to work.
